ABT 1256":"about 1256","1221":"1221","Aumale, Seine Maritime, Haute Normandie, France":"Aumale, Seine-Maritime, Upper Normandy, France","Abbaye Saint-Antoine-lès-Paris, Paris, 75000, Île-de-France, France":"Paris, Île-de-France, France","Toledo, Castilla, La Mancha, Spain":"Toledo, Castilla-La Mancha, Spain","Tunis, Aryanah, Tunésie":"Ariana, Tunisia","Montfort L'amaury, Seine-Et-Oise, France":"Montfort-l'Amaury, Seine-et-Oise, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Monfort","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French/Haitian Jacques, Marcel, Monique, Wilner.","French and Breton: habitational name from any of numerous places called Montfort, from Old French <i>mont</i> ‘hill’ (see   Mont   1) + <i>fort</i> ‘strong, impregnable’ (from Latin <i>fortis</i>). This surname is by far most common in Brittany. It is also found in Haiti. Compare   Montfort   1, see also 2 below.","Altered form of Dutch <b>Montfoort</b>, a variant of   Montfort   2 and also a cognate of the French name in 1 above and an altered form of its variant   Montfort   1 (or perhaps vice versa)."],"variants":[{"name":"Montfort","meanings":["French and Breton: variant of   Monfort   1. This surname is most common in Brittany and Haute-Savoie. See also 2 below.","Altered form of Dutch <b>Montfoort</b>: habitational name from Montfoort in Utrecht. It is a cognate of 1 above (see   Monfort   1) and also its altered form (or perhaps vice versa).","English (of Norman origin): very rare variant of   Mountford  , a cognate of 1 above."]},{"name":"Mont","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Carlos, Jose, Juan, Cristina, Domingo, Francisco, Jorge, Luis, Mariano, Ramon, Trinidad.","Catalan and French: topographic name for a mountain dweller, from Catalan and (Old) French <i>mont</i> ‘mountain’ (from Latin <i>mons</i>, genitive <i>montis</i>). Compare French   Demont   and   Dumont  .","English: variant of   Mount  ."]}]},{"name":"Laure","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin.  See  <b>Laura</b>   ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Laure Monfort D'epernon was born about 1240, in Montfort-l'Amaury, Seine-et-Oise, France, her father, Simon IV de MONFORT, was 49 and her mother, Alixe de Montmorency, was 21. She married Sancho Fernández, Arzobispo de Sevilla y de Toledo about 1256. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died on 25 July 1270, in Ariana, Tunisia, at the age of 31, and was buried in Paris, Île-de-France, France."},"et":{"ABT 1240–25 JUL 1270":"umbes 1240–25. juuli 1270","1240–1270":"1240–1270","1233–1261":"1233–1261","1255–1302":"1255–1302","1192–1241":"1192–1241","1221–1301":"1221–1301","1241":"1241","1240":"1240","1261":"1261","1270":"1270","1192":"1192","ABT 1240":"umbes 1240","1302":"1302","27 October 1261":"27. oktoober 1261","1301":"1301","1255":"1255","25 JUL 1270":"25. juuli 1270","1233":"1233","ABT 1256":"umbes 1256","1221":"1221","Aumale, Seine Maritime, Haute Normandie, France":"Aumale, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Abbaye Saint-Antoine-lès-Paris, Paris, 75000, Île-de-France, France":"Paris, Île-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Toledo, Castilla, La Mancha, Spain":"Toledo, Castilla-La Mancha, Hispaania","Tunis, Aryanah, Tunésie":"Ariana, Tuneesia","Montfort L'amaury, Seine-Et-Oise, France":"Montfort-l'Amaury, Seine-et-Oise, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"ABT 1240–25 JUL 1270":"noin 1240–25. heinäkuuta 1270","1240–1270":"1240–1270","1233–1261":"1233–1261","1255–1302":"1255–1302","1192–1241":"1192–1241","1221–1301":"1221–1301","1241":"1241","1240":"1240","1261":"1261","1270":"1270","1192":"1192","ABT 1240":"noin 1240","1302":"1302","27 October 1261":"27. lokakuuta 1261","1301":"1301","1255":"1255","25 JUL 1270":"25. heinäkuuta 1270","1233":"1233","ABT 1256":"noin 1256","1221":"1221","Aumale, Seine Maritime, Haute Normandie, France":"Aumale, Sein